        <!-- Quick Start -->
        <div class="doc-section framed neutral" id="quick-start">
            <div class="section-title">1. Quick Start Guide</div>
            <p>Welcome to Digimon X, the ultimate Digital Monster collection and farming simulator powered by AI!</p>
            
            <div class="info">
                <strong>First Time Trainer?</strong><br>
                Follow these 3 simple steps to become a Digimon Tamer!
            </div>

            <div class="command">
                <div class="command-name">Step 1: Social Verification</div>
                Visit our official X: <a href="https://x.com/digimononx" class="x-handle">@digimononx</a><br>
                Mention us to verify your Trainer account.
            </div>

            <div class="command">
                <div class="command-name">Step 2: Capture Your First Digimon</div>
                Use the <span class="highlight">/tamer</span> command to capture your first Digimon.<br>
                Each tamer can have up to <span class="highlight">THREE</span> Digimon in their party.
            </div>

            <div class="command">
                <div class="command-name">Step 3: Train and Battle</div>
                Check your Digimon with <span class="highlight">/digivice</span><br>
                Farm with other tamers using <span class="highlight">/farm</span>!
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Digimon Capture -->
        <div class="doc-section framed neutral" id="catching">
            <div class="section-title">2. Digimon Capture System</div>
            
            <p>Become a Digimon Tamer by capturing and training up to 3 Digimon!</p>

            <div class="warning">
                <strong>Digimon Limits</strong><br>
                • Maximum 3 Digimon per tamer<br>
                • Each capture attempt uses AI generation<br>
                • Digimon have unique stats and personalities<br>
                • Rare Digimon have special abilities
            </div>

            <div class="success">
                <strong>Catch Requirements</strong><br>
                1. Valid X (Twitter) account linked<br>
                2. Mention @PokettFun for verification<br>
                3. Available Digimon slots (max 3)<br>
                4. Ready to train and farm!
            </div>

            <div class="code-block">
                <div class="prompt">digimon-x --tamer</div>
                <pre>
> Wild Digimon appeared!
> Entering Digital World...
> Generating Digimon stats...
> Success! Agumon was captured!
> Level: 5 | Type: Fire
> Added to your party (1/3)
                </pre>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Commands -->
        <div class="doc-section framed neutral" id="commands">
            <div class="section-title">3. Command Reference</div>
            
            <p>Digimon X features comprehensive Digimon commands powered by AI generation.</p>

            <div class="command">
                <div class="command-name">/tamer</div>
                <strong>Purpose:</strong> Capture a wild Digimon for your party<br>
                <strong>Usage:</strong> <code>/tamer @your_x_handle</code><br>
                <strong>Cooldown:</strong> Success or failure determines next capture<br>
                <strong>Requirements:</strong> Available party slot (max 3)
            </div>

            <div class="command">
                <div class="command-name">/digivice</div>
                <strong>Purpose:</strong> Check your Digimon party status<br>
                <strong>Usage:</strong> <code>/digivice</code><br>
                <strong>Cooldown:</strong> None<br>
                <strong>Returns:</strong> All your Digimon stats and levels
            </div>

            <div class="command">
                <div class="command-name">/farm</div>
                <strong>Purpose:</strong> Farm with other tamers and your Digimon<br>
                <strong>Usage:</strong> <code>/farm</code><br>
                <strong>Cooldown:</strong> 5 minutes between farming<br>
                <strong>Rewards:</strong> XP, levels, rare items
            </div>

            <div class="info">
                <strong>PLANNED COMMANDS (Coming Soon)</strong><br>
                • /trade - Trade Digimon with other tamers<br>
                • /gym - Challenge Gym Leaders<br>
                • /tournament - Enter Digimon tournaments<br>
                • /digivolve - Digivolve your Digimon<br>
                • /team - Create farming teams
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- AI System -->
        <div class="doc-section framed neutral" id="ai-system">
            <div class="section-title">4. AI Digimon Generation</div>
            
            <p>Digimon X uses <span class="highlight">Advanced AI</span> to generate unique Digimon with individual stats, types, and abilities.</p>

            <div class="success">
                <strong>DIGIMON GENERATION SYSTEM</strong><br>
                Each Digimon is unique with:<br>
                • Randomized stats and IVs<br>
                • Type advantages and weaknesses<br>
                • Special moves and abilities<br>
                • Evolution potential<br>
                • Rare Digimon chances (1/100)
            </div>

            <div class="code-block">
                <div class="prompt">digimon-x --digimon-stats greymon</div>
                <pre>
> CHARIZARD - Fire/Flying Type
> Level: 36 | HP: 120/120
> Attack: 84 | Defense: 78 
> Sp.Atk: 109 | Sp.Def: 85
> Speed: 100
> Moves: Flamethrower, Dragon Claw, Air Slash, Heat Wave
> Ability: Blaze
                </pre>
            </div>

            <div class="warning">
                <strong>AI GENERATION FEATURES</strong><br>
                Every capture attempt generates a completely unique Digimon with balanced stats for fair gameplay!
            </div>

            <div class="info">
                <strong>DIGIMON RARITY TIERS</strong><br>
                Common (60%) | Uncommon (25%) | Rare (10%) | Epic (4%) | Legendary (1%)
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Digimon Care -->
        <div class="doc-section framed neutral" id="digimon-care">
            <div class="section-title">5. Digimon Care & Training</div>
            
            <p>Train your Digimon to increase their stats and prepare for farming!</p>

            <div class="command">
                <div class="command-name">Training Mechanics</div>
                • <strong>Feed System:</strong> 60-minute cooldown between feeds<br>
                • <strong>Berry Types:</strong> Different berries boost different stats<br>
                • <strong>Growth Stages:</strong> Baby → Teen → Adult<br>
                • <strong>Farm Ready:</strong> Higher level = more efficient farming
            </div>

            <div class="code-block">
                <div class="prompt">digimon-x --feed agumon --food=meat</div>
                <pre>
> Feeding Pikachu with Sitrus Berry...
> HP restored to full!
> Happiness increased!
> Growth: Baby → Teen (3/6 feeds)
> Next feeding in: 59 minutes
                </pre>
            </div>

            <div class="success">
                <strong>TRAINING EVENTS</strong><br>
                Special events for trainers:<br>
                • Double XP weekends<br>
                • Legendary Digimon appearances<br>
                • Community day events<br>
                • Rare Digimon increased rates
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Growth System -->
        <div class="doc-section framed neutral" id="growth-system">
            <div class="section-title">6. Evolution System</div>
            
            <p>Digimon digivolve through feeding and battling, unlocking new forms and abilities!</p>

            <div class="info">
                <strong>GROWTH STAGES</strong><br>
                <strong>Baby (0-2 feeds):</strong> Starting stats, learning moves<br>
                <strong>Teen (3-5 feeds):</strong> Stat boosts, new abilities<br>
                <strong>Adult (6+ feeds):</strong> Full power, evolution ready<br>
                <strong>Champion (10+ wins):</strong> Elite stats, rare moves<br>
                <strong>Master (50+ wins):</strong> Legendary status
            </div>

            <div class="warning">
                <strong>EVOLUTION TRIGGERS</strong><br>
                Digimon digivolve based on:<br>
                • Feed count milestones<br>
                • Battle victories<br>
                • Level thresholds<br>
                • Special items (coming soon)
            </div>

            <div class="code-block">
                <div class="prompt">digimon-x --digivolution greymon</div>
                <pre>
> CHARMELEON Evolution Status:
> Current Level: 35
> Evolution: CHARIZARD at Level 36
> Progress: 95% Complete
> 
> Stats Preview after evolution:
> HP: 78 → 120 (+42)
> Attack: 64 → 84 (+20)
> New Type: Fire/Flying
> New Move: Air Slash
                </pre>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Social Features -->
        <div class="doc-section framed neutral" id="social-features">
            <div class="section-title">7. Trainer Community</div>
            
            <p>Join the Digimon X tamer community and compete for the top spots!</p>

            <div class="success">
                <strong>SOCIAL FEATURES</strong><br>
                • Auto-share Digimon captures to X<br>
                • Trainer leaderboards<br>
                • Battle tournaments<br>
                • Digimon trading (coming soon)<br>
                • Team farming (coming soon)
            </div>

            <div class="command">
                <div class="command-name">Community Events</div>
                <strong>Weekly Tournaments:</strong> Battle for rare Digimon<br>
                <strong>Legendary Raids:</strong> Team up to capture legendaries<br>
                <strong>Trading Days:</strong> Exchange Digimon with others<br>
                <strong>Shiny Hunts:</strong> Increased shiny rates
            </div>

            <div class="info">
                <strong>LEADERBOARDS</strong><br>
                • Top Tamers: Most farming success<br>
                • Digimon Masters: Most Digimon captured<br>
                • Battle Champions: Highest win streaks<br>
                • Rare Collectors: Most rare Digimon<br>
                • Elite Four: Top 4 trainers globally
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Technical -->
        <div class="doc-section framed neutral" id="technical">
            <div class="section-title">8. Technical Specifications</div>
            
            <p>Digimon X runs on modern infrastructure for the best Digimon experience.</p>

            <div class="code-block">
                <div class="prompt">digimon-x --system-info</div>
                <pre>
> Digimon X System v1.0.0
>
> Backend: Node.js + Express.js
> Database: SQLite3
> AI Engine: Advanced Digimon Generation
> Frontend: Digimon Digital Theme
> Authentication: X (Twitter) OAuth
> Hosting: High-performance servers
> Updates: Real-time farming system
> Features: Auto-feeding, Evolution tracking
                </pre>
            </div>

            <div class="warning">
                <strong>🔒 SECURITY MEASURES</strong><br>
                • Military-grade encryption for all user data<br>
                • Regular security audits by third-party firms<br>
                • GDPR and CCPA compliant data handling<br>
                • No personal data sold or shared with advertisers<br>
                • Open-source security modules for transparency
            </div>

            <div class="success">
                <strong>⚡ PERFORMANCE METRICS</strong><br>
                • Average response time: <200ms globally<br>
                • 99.9% uptime guarantee with SLA<br>
                • Supports 100,000+ concurrent users<br>
                • Auto-scaling infrastructure handles traffic spikes<br>
                • CDN distribution across 50+ global regions
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- API -->
        <div class="doc-section" id="api">
            <div class="section-title">🔌 9. Developer API Documentation</div>
            
            <div class="warning">
                <strong>📝 NOTE: API NOT AVAILABLE YET</strong><br>
                The developer API is currently under development and not available during early access.<br>
                We are working hard to provide comprehensive API endpoints for the community.<br>
                Expected release: Q2 2025 with full documentation and developer tools.
            </div>

            <p>Digimon X will provide comprehensive APIs for developers building integrations, bots, and third-party applications once we exit early access phase.</p>

            <div class="info">
                <strong>🚧 PLANNED API FEATURES</strong><br>
                • Pet information retrieval endpoints<br>
                • Authenticated feeding and care actions<br>
                • Real-time WebSocket connections<br>
                • Social media integration tools<br>
                • Community event participation<br>
                • Leaderboard and statistics access
            </div>

            <div class="success">
                <strong>🔔 GET NOTIFIED</strong><br>
                Join our Discord or follow @PokettFun on X to be notified when the API becomes available.<br>
                Early access developers will receive priority access to beta API endpoints.
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Troubleshooting -->
        <div class="doc-section" id="troubleshooting">
            <div class="section-title">🔧 10. Troubleshooting & Support</div>
            
            <div class="warning">
                <strong>❌ COMMON ISSUES</strong><br>
                <strong>Problem:</strong> "Pet not responding to commands"<br>
                <strong>Solution:</strong> Check feeding status - hungry pets have reduced responsiveness<br><br>
                
                <strong>Problem:</strong> "Cannot claim pet - account already verified"<br>
                <strong>Solution:</strong> Each X account can only claim one pet. Contact support for assistance<br><br>
                
                <strong>Problem:</strong> "Evolution not triggering despite meeting requirements"<br>
                <strong>Solution:</strong> Evolution has random factors. Try interacting more frequently
            </div>

        </div>

        <!-- Community -->
        <div class="doc-section framed neutral" id="community">
            <div class="section-title">11. Trainer Guidelines</div>
            
            <p>Digimon X tamers follow the Digimon Tamer code of conduct.</p>

            <div class="success">
                <strong>TRAINER CODE</strong><br>
                • Share Digimon captures and victories<br>
                • Help new trainers get started<br>
                • Participate in tournaments<br>
                • Report bugs and glitches<br>
                • Respect all trainers<br>
                • Celebrate rare captures
            </div>

            <div class="warning">
                <strong>PROHIBITED ACTIVITIES</strong><br>
                • Multi-account Digimon farming<br>
                • Bot usage for farming<br>
                • Harassment of trainers<br>
                • Exploit abuse<br>
                • Selling Digimon for real money<br>
                • Impersonating gym leaders
            </div>

            <div class="info">
                <strong>🏛️ GOVERNANCE SYSTEM</strong><br>
                Digimon X employs a democratic governance model where community members vote on major decisions:<br>
                • New feature priorities<br>
                • Evolution system changes<br>
                • Community event themes<br>
                • Disciplinary action appeals<br>
                • Partnership and collaboration approvals
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Changelog -->
        <div class="doc-section" id="changelog">
            <div class="section-title">📝 12. Version History & Roadmap</div>
            
            <div class="code-block">
                <div class="prompt">digimon-x --version-history</div>
                <pre>
> VERSION 1.0.0 (Current) - July 25, 2025 - EARLY ACCESS LAUNCH
